Title: Ellie & Andrea's Escalator Mall Adventure: Safety Learning for Kids
Description:
Join Ellie and Andrea on a fun adventure at the mall! They discover the excitement and challenges of riding escalators, shopping for toys, and even enjoying tasty pretzels. Along the way, they learn important lessons about safety, like taking one step at a time on escalators, not running, and always being aware of their surroundings. Watch as they bravely conquer their fears and have a blast together.

Lesson Learned:
It's important to be safe and aware of your surroundings while having fun. Taking things one step at a time can make even the scariest tasks manageable!

Title: Ellie Eva & Eric Learn Science with Balloon Pop Experiments for Kids
Description:
Uncle Jim, Ellie, Eva, and Eric do the science experiment "Pop or No Pop!" Uncle Jim conducts fun balloon experiments to see if they pop or not. Ellie and Eva make their guesses, but the results surprise everyone! Learn about science with Uncle Jim as he explains why balloons behave differently with various objects like nails and needles. Discover the magic of static electricity with a pepper experiment, and see how a needle can pass through a balloon without popping it. This video is full of fun and educational moments that teach kids about pressure, static electricity, and the properties of balloons.

Lesson Learned:
Science can be fun and surprising! Through these experiments, kids learn about the concepts of pressure, static electricity, and material properties. They discover how spreading force over a larger area can prevent a balloon from popping and how static electricity can attract objects.

Welcome to LiaChaCha, where we invite you into the world of Lia and ChaCha, adorable twins navigating the ups and downs of siblinghood. Title: Police car, JCB Excavator, Construction Vehicles catch thief - Toy for kids
Description:
Police car, JCB Excavator, Construction Vehicles catch thief
In this hilarious and heartwarming story, we see a group of unlikely heroes come together to save the day. When a pair of thieves try to steal a police car, they end up getting in over their heads and falling into a nearby lake. Luckily, the police officers on duty are quick to act and use a flotation device to rescue the struggling thieves.

But the story doesn't end there. The officers then call upon a team of construction vehicles, including a bulldozer and a excavator, to help retrieve the submerged cars from the water. With their combined efforts, the vehicles are able to lift the cars out of the lake and return them to dry land.

This story is not only entertaining and silly, but it also teaches children about the importance of teamwork and helping others in need. Even in the face of danger, the police officers and construction vehicles work together to ensure everyone is safe and that the stolen property is recovered. It shows that even those who may seem like enemies at first, can come together for a common goal and make a positive difference in the world.

By sharing stories like this with children, we can help instill important values such as kindness, cooperation, and compassion. It shows them that no matter how big or small they may be, they have the power to make a difference and help those in need. And who knows, maybe one day they'll be the ones driving the construction vehicles, saving the day and making the world a better place.

Title: WHAT I GOT MY KIDS FOR CHRISTMAS 2024 VLOGMAS @BriannaK
Description:
Sharing what I got my kids for christmas 2024! Hi, I'm Brianna, and I'm a mom of 3 kids- Landon is a 9 year old boy, Presley is a 7 year old girl, and Hayden is a 4 year old boy. I couldn't have made this Christmas possible for my kids as a single mom if it weren't for YOU watching my videos and supporting this channel. THANK YOU, THANK YOU, THANK YOU from the bottom of my heart. I am so very grateful, and this is an absolute dream come true to be a mom and make Christmas magical for my three babies. I'm so excited to see their faces on Christmas morning!! Hope this video gives you some gift ideas if your kids or loved ones are around the same ages for christmas or  birthday gifts!  Wishing you all the merriest christmas and the happiest New Year!! 
Love,
Brianna K xoxo

Title: We Rescued Kids Living in a Garbage Dump
Description:
When young children have to dig through toxic landfills in hopes of earning enough money to buy a simple bowl of rice, we have failed as humans.  This is not an Indian problem. It is a global problem that should bother each and every one of us. Poverty has no boundaries. Please don‚Äôt look the other way anymore. Together we can fix it by supporting incredible groups like Tiljala Shed (https://tished.org/). 

Sometimes we see a problem that seems so insurmountable that we ignore it thinking ‚ÄúWhat difference will $5 make?‚Äù  It makes a huge difference because thousands of small donations add up very fast, but thousands of people deciding their contribution is too small to make a difference leads nowhere. Please give what you can. Apathy is our enemy. 

Started by Alamgir, and now run by his son Shafkat, Tiljala Shed is an outstanding organization. They are committed to helping as many children as possible by giving them dignity and opportunity. Please consider donating to help.
https://tished.org/donate/
International Donors: https://goto.gg/32034
Indian Donors: https://give.do/fundraisers/tiljala-shed-education

While we were in India we were told many of the children in the program came from households where there was not enough food to eat every day. Massive shoutout to The Smith Brothers Family Foundation for their incredibly generous donation to feed all these families for the next two years.

And finally, in a shocking, yet unsurprising (I know that doesn‚Äôt make sense, but its how I feel)  act of generosity, Tony and Sage Robbins, after watching a prescreening of the video, instantly offered to support this entire program, including the at-home meals for these kids and their families 
for an entire additional year. 

https://www.thetonyrobbinsfoundation.org/
https://www.instagram.com/sagerobbins/

Poverty is a global problem. What is depicted in our videos is not intended to represent the entire country, or its people. Every country has its poor.  We wish to draw attention to the issues that challenge humanity across the planet, build empathy, offer relief where we can, and inspire others to do the same. We can only change the world together.

Filmed and Edited by: Dan Mace ( https://www.youtube.com/@DanMace)

ABOUT 'GOT TALENT'
Got Talent is a British talent show TV format developed by Simon Cowell's SYCOtv company and owned by Fremantle Media Ltd. It has spawned spin-offs in over 70 countries, in what is now referred to as the 'Got Talent' format, similar to that described by Fremantle of the 'Idol' and 'The X Factor' singing show competition formats. Unlike those shows, Got Talent showcases a wide variety of artistic disciplines in addition to singing.

'Got Talent' was named the world's most successful reality TV format ever by Guinness World Records. Cowell stated, ‚ÄúI am very proud that Got Talent is a home grown British show. We owe its success to a group of very talented producers all over the world who have made this happen. And of course amazing talent.‚Äù

ABOUT TOP 10 TALENT 
Top 10 Talent is a YouTube channel that selects and showcases the best performances from Got Talent, Idol, and X Factor shows around the world from America's Got Talent, Britain's Got Talent, Pilipinas Got Talent, India's Got Talent, Canada's Got Talent, Ukraine's Got Talent and so many more...
